cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.CR 

This paper discusses user access patterns in web archives, which involves information retrieval (IR) and digital libraries (DL). It also touches upon human-computer interaction (HC) and cybersecurity (CY) as it discusses the differences in access patterns between humans and robots. Additionally, it mentions the potential for web archives to be used in criminal investigations, which falls under the category of computer security (CR).
